The paper introduces a dynamic programming method for solving reconfiguration problems, which involves manipulating graphs and finding paths between them. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Additionally, the paper involves solving optimization problems, which could place it in the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with graph theory and combinatorial optimization, which could place it in the categories of cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
